cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on optimizing server energy consumption and cost in data center server setups. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes two modes of aggregation to compute optimal configurations in near real-time for large scale data centers. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with dynamic temporal workload and proposes dynamic aggregation methods. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper presents formulations to minimize server energy consumption and cost. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a methodology to understand the trade-off in energy-aware aggregation.
